The paper deals with a fundamental graph problem of counting induced subgraphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The focus is on sparse graphs, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a novel notion of graph width, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
